main event: Two unidentified objects were detected and tracked on ground radar near Bremerton, Washington in July 1962.
interesting points: The objects were detected and tracked by a ground radar site, but no visual confirmation could be made due to overcast and rainy weather conditions.
The report does not provide details on the size, speed or altitude of the objects.
The Air Force considered the sighting to potentially be a shooting star or other astronomical phenomenon based on the limited information available.
In a follow-up letter, the Air Force stated that their records did not reveal any published stories or pictures in the Seattle Times about unidentified objects and Air Force jets in the area.
A high school student wrote a letter expressing interest in UFOs and requesting the Air Force's views on whether they could be interplanetary vehicles.
sighted object: two unidentified objects detected on ground radar
